TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: Format the insert by building the INSRT_TS and the APPL_INSRT_NM fields.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: EXP_Format_Insert

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This lookup is meant to determine if there is already a summary entry in the RCNT_RECN_SUMM_QUE table for the same RECN_GID/MODEL/CORP/RECN_SUMM_TYP_CD, where the RECN_SUMM_STAT_CD = 1 (new, awaiting summary). There should not be more than one entry with that status. If an entry already exists, do not send the insert to the target.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: LKP_RCNT_RECN_SUMM_QUE_Already_Exists

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup condition
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: RECN_GID = RECN_GID_in AND MODEL_TYP_CD = MODEL_TYP_CD_in AND CORP_CD = CORP_CD_in AND RECN_SUMM_TYP_CD = RECN_SUMM_TYP_CD_in AND RECN_SUMM_STAT_CD = RECN_SUMM_STAT_CD_in

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: If the input RECN_SUMM_GID is null, that means no record was found in the LKP_RCNT_RECN_SUMM_QUE_Already_Exists lookup, and a row needs to be inserted into the target. If the RECN_SUMM_GID is not null, then there is already a row in the target table waiting to be summarized.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: RTR_Rows_to_Insert

GROUP.DESCRIPTION: Path for the data when none of the group conditions are satisfied.
GROUP.NAME: DEFAULT1

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This source qualifier will select DISTINCT MODEL_TYP_CD, RECN_GIDs for the RECN_GID from the parameter table
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: SQ_Get_Recon_Rows

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT DISTINCT MID.MODEL_TYP_CD ,RH.RECN_GID FROM VRAP.RCNT_RECN_HDR RH ,VRAP.RCNT_RBAT_MFG_INV_HDR MIH ,VRAP.RCNT_RBAT_MFG_INV_DTL MID , VRAP.RCNT_RECN_PARAM PRM WHERE RH.RECN_GID = MIH.RECN_GID AND MIH.INV_ID = MID.INV_ID AND MID.HVST_ID=PRM.HVST_ID AND RH.RECN_GID = PRM.RECN_GID

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This expression will bring in the SQ results, and the CORP_CD from the LKP_TCORP_MODEL_TYP_CD, and build the RECN_SUMM_TYP_CD values that the Normalizer needs in order to build the three different inserts for the three different types. 1 = Recon Position Summary 2 = Recon Variance Summary 3 = Recon Dispute Summary Also format the insert for the RCNT_RECN_ACTN_STUS table.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: EXP_Build_NRM_New_Recon_RCNT_RECN_SUMM_QUE

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: 10/28/14 SP - Look up the dummy distribution (stat_cd of 91) to use in the dstr summary table
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: LKP_RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR_DSTR_GID

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup Sql Override
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT MAX(HDR.DSTR_GID) as DSTR_GID, HDR.RECN_GID as RECN_GID FROM VRAP.RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR HDR, (SELECT DISTINCT RECN_GID FROM VRAP.RCNT_RECN_PARAM) PRM WHERE HDR.RECN_GID = PRM.RECN_GID AND HDR.DSTR_STAT_CD = $$PARM_RECN_DSTR_TYP_DUMMY GROUP by HDR.RECN_GID

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT CLM.RECN_GID, CLM.MODEL_TYP_CD, CLM.COMMON_DRUG_NM, CLM.PICO_ID, CLM.ADMN_PEND_DSTR_AMT, CLM.BASE_PEND_DSTR_AMT, CLM.PERF_PEND_DSTR_AMT, CLM.FRMLY_PEND_DSTR_AMT, CLM.CTRC_PEND_DSTR_AMT, CLM.PRC_PTCT_PEND_DSTR_AMT, CLM.ADMN_PEND_ADJ_AMT, CLM.BASE_PEND_ADJ_AMT, CLM.PERF_PEND_ADJ_AMT, CLM.FRMLY_PEND_ADJ_AMT, CLM.CTRC_PEND_ADJ_AMT, CLM.PRC_PTCT_PEND_ADJ_AMT, CLM.RPT_AP_CO_CD FROM VRAP.RCNT_RECN_EXTN_CLM CLM, (SELECT DISTINCT RECN_GID FROM VRAP.RCNT_RECN_PARAM )PRM WHERE CLM.RECN_GID = PRM.RECN_GID AND CLM.RECN_SCRB_CD <> $$PARM_SCRB_CD

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: 10/28/14 SP - Look up the dummy distribution (stat_cd of 91) to use in the dstr summary table
INSTANCE.NAME: LKP_RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR_DSTR_GID

SESSION.DESCRIPTION: This session summarizes records for the specific reconciliations and inserts into VRAP.RCNT_RECN_DSTR_SUMM. This session is meant to create entries for Dummy DSTR_GIDs to give the UI a place to start transactions/distributions. Since this is an INSERT only, there could be duplicate records (for copy-void reconciliations). But that is OK.
SESSION.NAME: s_m_CASH_Insert_RCNT_RECN_DSTR_SUMM_NEW

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Post SQL
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE: UPDATE VRAP.RCNT_RECN_HDR SET RECN_STAT_CD = $$PARM_RECN_READY WHERE RECN_GID in (SELECT DISTINCT RECN_GID FROM VRAP.RCNT_RECN_PARAM)
